The paper deals with detecting suspicious behavior in large online networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC), data mining (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the weaknesses of current methods for detecting fraudulent behavior, which could be considered a security issue (cs.CR). Finally, the proposed algorithm has theoretical underpinnings and is evaluated on real data, which suggests that it could fall under the category of social influence (cs.SI).
